# Up Final Business Model Rule

## Product Tiers (Fixed)
- **Core App (one-time purchase)** unlocks all local features:
  - Assessment calculation
  - Six-axis radar display
  - Personal history records
  - Widgets
- **Pro Service (monthly subscription)** unlocks:
  - Global leaderboard access (view + upload)
  - Cloud sync capabilities

## Access Control
- Entitlement logic must be centralized in `src/logic/core` (single source of truth).
- Leaderboard entry and upload must require valid Pro status.
- Core local data must remain available without Pro.

## Schema Requirements
- User profile must reserve subscription fields such as:
  - `purchase_status`
  - `subscription_status`
  - `is_pro`
  - `pro_expires_at`
  - `plan_id`

## Firebase Cost Guardrails
- Non-Pro users must not trigger Firestore leaderboard read/write traffic.
- Leaderboard documents should store summary-only fields (best score + minimal profile).
- Add leaderboard caching to avoid repeated reads.
- Add write throttling (for example, hourly upload cap per user).
- Skip Firestore write when public score is unchanged (2dp); allow better or worse scores to write (rank trial / revert).

## UX Requirements
- Entering leaderboard must run subscription checks first.
- If not eligible, show a value-driven upgrade flow ("join arena") instead of a generic lock screen.
- Pro badge should be visible in leaderboard-related UI with a premium but restrained style.
